<node CREATED="1283910045448" ID="ID_1029252822" MODIFIED="1283910049862" TEXT="PEP 257 &#x63d0;&#x5230; &#x201c;A docstring is a string literal that occurs as the first statement in a module, function, class, or method definition. Such a docstring becomes the __doc__ special attribute of that object.&#x201d;"/>
<node CREATED="1283910016502" ID="ID_126065609" MODIFIED="1290497915185" TEXT="Docstrings are accessible via a Python object&#x2019;s __doc__ attribute. This is very helpful if you are testing out a new module in Python&#x2019;s interactive shell and really need to know what sort of parameters a certain function needs."/>
<node CREATED="1283910107244" ID="ID_1832312116" MODIFIED="1283910249078" TEXT="Docstrings &#x53ea;&#x662f;&#x7279;&#x6b8a;&#x7684; Comments &#x800c;&#x5df2;, &#x6c92;&#x6709;&#x683c;&#x5f0f;&#x4e0a;&#x7684;&#x8981;&#x6c42;. &#x4f46;&#x5982;&#x679c;&#x80fd;&#x9806;&#x8457; Style Guidelines &#x8d70;, Docstring &#x5beb;&#x8d77;&#x4f86;&#x6703;&#x66f4;&#x6709;&#x7cfb;&#x7d71;, &#x5225;&#x4eba;&#x4e5f;&#x66f4;&#x5bb9;&#x6613;&#x770b;&#x5f97;&#x61c2;">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1284011604313" ID="ID_1060221335" MODIFIED="1284011608903" TEXT="When you are writing your docstrings, you aren&#x2019;t just commenting your source code you&#x2019;re also writing your help file!"/>
<node CREATED="1284018899759" ID="ID_1711881454" MODIFIED="1284018901615" TEXT="The documentation is extracted directly from the sources, which makes it much easier to keep the documentation consistent with the source code.">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1283911483166" ID="ID_1542191517" MODIFIED="1284006145041" TEXT="Concepts">
<node CREATED="1283910297740" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_276188487" MODIFIED="1283910346669" TEXT="One-Line/Multi-Line Docstrings">
<node CREATED="1283910337003" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1732198078" MODIFIED="1283910338775" TEXT="One-Line">
<node CREATED="1283911040107" ID="ID_1113048198" MODIFIED="1283911071874" TEXT="Triple quotes are used even though the string fits on one line. This makes it easy to later expand it.  (&#x4e0d;&#x8981;&#x54ea;&#x5929;&#x88e1;&#x9762;&#x7528;&#x5230;&#x5176;&#x4ed6;&#x5f15;&#x865f;&#x6642;, &#x624d;&#x4f86;&#x6539;&#x6700;&#x5916;&#x5c64;&#x7684;&#x5f15;&#x865f;)"/>
<node CREATED="1283911040117" ID="ID_1085833591" MODIFIED="1283912558223" TEXT="There&#x2019;s no blank line either before or after the doc string.">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1283911040118" ID="ID_569845777" MODIFIED="1283911112932" TEXT="The doc string is a phrase ending in a period. It prescribes the function&#x2019;s effect as a command (&#x201c;Do this&#x201d;, &#x201c;Return that&#x201d;), not as a description: e.g. don&#x2019;t write &#x201c;Returns the pathname &#x2026;&#x201d; (&#x5982;&#x679c;&#x8981;&#x63cf;&#x8ff0;&#x66f4;&#x591a;&#x7684;&#x7d30;&#x7bc0;, &#x61c9;&#x8a72;&#x6539;&#x7528; Multi-Line Docstrings)"/>
<node CREATED="1283910762861" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_156737732" MODIFIED="1283910764357" TEXT="Example">
<node CREATED="1283910381809" ID="ID_1584289749" MODIFIED="1283910383699" TEXT="def add(x, y):&#xa;    &quot;&quot;&quot;Return the sum of two numbers.&quot;&quot;&quot;&#xa;    return x + y"/>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1283910338992" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_280307949" MODIFIED="1283910343690" TEXT="Multi-Line">
<node CREATED="1283911264473" ID="ID_1912487481" MODIFIED="1283911294722" TEXT="Multi-line docstrings should be used to documents the input, output, and complex behaviour of your objects."/>
<node CREATED="1283911272720" ID="ID_1215508082" MODIFIED="1283911294731" TEXT="Like one-line docstrings, multi-line docstrings should start with a single sentence summary. After that there should be a blank line and then a more detailed description."/>
<node CREATED="1283911287398" ID="ID_1099705981" MODIFIED="1283911294745" TEXT="The blank line separating the one line summary and the additional information is important as certain tools will use the blank line to separate the summary from the rest of the docstring.">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1283911171290" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_930861619" MODIFIED="1283912657866" TEXT="Examples">
<node CREATED="1283911174670" ID="ID_536739828" MODIFIED="1283912895799" TEXT="def subtract(x, y):&#xa;    &quot;&quot;&quot;Return the difference between two numbers. &lt;-- &#x5beb;&#x5728;&#x8207;&#x958b;&#x982d;&#x7684; &quot;&quot;&quot; &#x540c;&#x4e00;&#x884c;&#xa;&#xa;    Arguments:&#xa;    x -- The minuend.&#xa;    y -- The subtrahend.&#xa;&#xa;    Returns:&#xa;    A number, the difference between x and y (ie. x - y)&#xa;&#xa;    &quot;&quot;&quot; &lt;-- &#x7fd2;&#x6163;&#x4e0a;&#x524d;&#x9762;&#x6703;&#x52a0;&#x4e00;&#x884c;&#x7a7a;&#x767d;, &#x5f8c;&#x9762;&#x5247;&#x7dca;&#x63a5;&#x8457; Statements&#xa;    return x - y"/>
<node CREATED="1283912660919" ID="ID_846104313" MODIFIED="1283912662637" TEXT="def complex(real=0.0, imag=0.0):&#xa;    &quot;&quot;&quot;Form a complex number.&#xa;&#xa;    Keyword arguments:&#xa;    real -- the real part (default 0.0)&#xa;    imag -- the imaginary part (default 0.0)&#xa;&#xa;    &quot;&quot;&quot;&#xa;    if imag == 0.0 and real == 0.0: return complex_zero&#xa;    ...&#xa;"/>
</node>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1283911489405" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1201941048" MODIFIED="1283911494168" TEXT="What to Document">
<node CREATED="1283911515625" ID="ID_1857411684" MODIFIED="1283911515625" TEXT="Modules &#x2013; Document the module and provide a one line summary of everything that is exported by the module. (eg. classes, exceptions, and functions)."/>
<node CREATED="1283911515631" ID="ID_997353144" MODIFIED="1283911515631" TEXT="Classes &#x2013; Summarize the functionality of the class. List all public methods and data members of the class. If there is any addition information needed to subclass the class, or if there is an additional interface for subclasses provide a description."/>
<node CREATED="1283911515667" ID="ID_436402588" MODIFIED="1283980910226" TEXT="Functions and Methods &#x2013; Summarize the functionality of the function and &#x201c;document its arguments, return value(s), side effects, exceptions raised, and restrictions on when it can be called (all if applicable).&#x201d; &#x9084;&#x6709;&#x4f7f;&#x7528;&#x7bc4;&#x4f8b;&#x4e5f;&#x53ef;&#x4ee5;&#x5beb;&#x9032;&#x53bb;, &#x8f14;&#x4ee5; doctest &#x505a;&#x6e2c;&#x8a66;&#x5c31;&#x66f4;&#x5999;&#x4e86;!!">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1283912081840" ID="ID_718634097" MODIFIED="1283914168851" TEXT="Examples">
<node CREATED="1283914438702" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1171987878" MODIFIED="1283914440533" TEXT="Example 1">
<node CREATED="1283912083787" ID="ID_1282235362" MODIFIED="1283912085371" TEXT="#!/usr/bin/env python&#xa;&quot;&quot;&quot;A simple math module.&#xa;&#xa;Exported Classes:&#xa;&#xa;Math -- A simple math class with mathematical functions.&#xa;&#xa;&quot;&quot;&quot;&#xa;&#xa;class Math(object):&#xa;    &quot;&quot;&quot;A simple math class with mathematical functions.&#xa;&#xa;    Public functions:&#xa;    add -- Adds two numbers together and&#xa;    returns the result.&#xa;&#xa;    subtract -- Returns the difference between&#xa;    two numbers.&#xa;&#xa;    &quot;&quot;&quot;&#xa;&#xa;    def subtract(self, x, y):&#xa;        &quot;&quot;&quot;Return the difference between two numbers.&#xa;&#xa;        Arguments:&#xa;        x -- The minuend.&#xa;        y -- The subtrahend.&#xa;&#xa;        Returns:&#xa;        A number, the difference between x and y (ie. x - y)&#xa;&#xa;        &quot;&quot;&quot;&#xa;        return x - y&#xa;&#xa;    def add(self, x, y):&#xa;        &quot;&quot;&quot;Return the sum of two numbers.&#xa;&#xa;        Arguments:&#xa;        x -- Number to be summed.&#xa;        y -- Number to be summed.&#xa;&#xa;        Returns:&#xa;        A number, the sum of x and y (ie. x + y)&#xa;&#xa;        &quot;&quot;&quot;&#xa;        return x + y"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1283914431253" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_475809113" MODIFIED="1283914433519" TEXT="Example 2">
<node CREATED="1283914170332" ID="ID_1513194749" MODIFIED="1283914172053" TEXT="#!/usr/bin/env python&#xa;&quot;&quot;&quot;A simple math module.&#xa;&#xa;Exported Classes:&#xa;&#xa;Math -- A simple math class with mathematical functions.&#xa;&#xa;&quot;&quot;&quot;&#xa;&#xa;class Math(object):&#xa;    &quot;&quot;&quot;A simple math class with mathematical functions.&#xa;&#xa;    Public functions:&#xa;    add -- Adds two numbers together and&#xa;    returns the result.&#xa;&#xa;    subtract -- Returns the difference between&#xa;    two numbers.&#xa;&#xa;    &quot;&quot;&quot;&#xa;&#xa;    def subtract(self, x, y):&#xa;        &quot;&quot;&quot;Return the difference between two numbers.&#xa;&#xa;        @type   x: number&#xa;        @param  x: The minuend.&#xa;        @type   y: number&#xa;        @param  y: The subtrahend.&#xa;&#xa;        @rtype: number&#xa;        @returns: A number, the difference between x and y (ie. x - y)&#xa;&#xa;        &quot;&quot;&quot;&#xa;        return x - y&#xa;&#xa;    def add(self, x, y):&#xa;        &quot;&quot;&quot;Return the sum of two numbers.&#xa;&#xa;        @type   x: number&#xa;        @param  x: Number to be summed.&#xa;        @type   y: number&#xa;        @param  y: Number to be summed.&#xa;&#xa;        @rtype: number&#xa;        @returns: A number, the sum of x and y (ie. x + y)&#xa;&#xa;        &quot;&quot;&quot;&#xa;        return x + y&#xa;&#xa;def _test():&#xa;    import doctest&#xa;    doctest.testmod()&#xa;&#xa;if __name__ == &quot;__main__&quot;:&#xa;    _test()"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1283914415400" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_612621684" MODIFIED="1283914421408" TEXT="Example 3">
<node CREATED="1283914422970" ID="ID_288932442" MODIFIED="1283914427051" TEXT="def _findGroupIdByName(group_name):&#xa;    &quot;&quot;&quot;Translate the group name into a corresponding group identifier in the backend system.&#xa;&#xa;    Arguments:&#xa;    group_name -- A string, group name to be found.&#xa;&#xa;    Returns:&#xa;    An integer, &#xa;&#xa;    Raises Exception on failure.&#xa;&#xa;    &quot;&quot;&quot;&#xa;"/>
</node>
