<node CREATED="1284014697332" ID="ID_1078421982" MODIFIED="1284014832849" TEXT="It does not mark up your docstrings. It simply reads them from your source code and spits them back out. &#x4e0d;&#x6703;&#x89e3;&#x8b80;&#x5d4c;&#x5728; Docstrings &#x88e1;&#x7684; Markup Language, &#x8981;&#x6539;&#x7528;&#x5176;&#x4ed6; Tools &#x50cf;&#x662f; Epydoc &#x6216; Docutils &#x624d;&#x884c;"/>
<node CREATED="1284014415500" ID="ID_276765550" MODIFIED="1284014505527" TEXT="If name contains a &apos;/&apos;, it is treated as a file&#x2010;name; if it names a directory, documentation is written for all the contents. (&#x9810;&#x8a2d;&#x662f;&#x7d66;&#x5b9a; Module Name, &#x5982;&#x679c; Module Name &#x5305;&#x542b;&#x6709; &apos;/&apos; &#x7684;&#x8a71;, &#x5c31;&#x8996;&#x70ba; .py &#x6216;&#x5305;&#x542b; .py &#x7684;&#x76ee;&#x9304;)"/>
