</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1281578628629" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1974822305" MODIFIED="1281578629715" TEXT="Option">
<node CREATED="1281579560179" ID="ID_427026491" MODIFIED="1301459340549" TEXT="An argument used to supply &apos;&apos;extra information&apos;&apos; to guide or customize the execution of a program. (&#x5ee3;&#x7fa9;&#x4f86;&#x8aaa;, option &#x78ba;&#x5be6;&#x662f; arguments &#x7684;&#x4e00;&#x54e1;&#xff0c;&#x9019;&#x88e1;&#x7684; &quot;extra&quot; &#x525b;&#x597d;&#x8ddf;&#x4e0b;&#x9762; positional argument &#x7684; &apos;required&apos; &#x6210;&#x5c0d;&#x6bd4;)"/>
<node CREATED="1286345368144" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_93022631" MODIFIED="1286345487651" TEXT="There are many different syntaxes for options (&#x4e0d;&#x904e;&#x662f; &#x5169;&#x7a2e; short/long options &#x5169;&#x7a2e;&#x8868;&#x793a;&#x6cd5;)">
<node CREATED="1286345390138" ID="ID_532139552" MODIFIED="1286345418822" TEXT="The traditional Unix syntax is a hyphen (&#x201c;`-`&#x201c;) followed by a single letter, e.g. &quot;`-x`&quot; or &quot;`-F`&quot;. Also, traditional Unix syntax allows multiple options to be merged into a single argument, e.g. &quot;`-x -F`&quot; is equivalent to &quot;`-xF`&quot;."/>
<node CREATED="1286345419624" ID="ID_1841234904" MODIFIED="1286345420193" TEXT="The GNU project introduced &quot;`--`&quot; followed by a series of &apos;&apos;hyphen-separated words&apos;&apos;, e.g. &quot;`--file`&quot; or &quot;`--dry-run`&quot;."/>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1281578629923" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_668927353" MODIFIED="1281578632896" TEXT="Option Argument">
<node CREATED="1281580352203" ID="ID_1065801516" MODIFIED="1281580356634" TEXT="An argument that follows an option, is closely associated with that option, and is consumed from the argument list when that option is."/>
<node CREATED="1286345612734" ID="ID_1539464512" MODIFIED="1301459123202" TEXT="Option arguments may either be in a separate argument from their option; &#x4f8b;&#x5982; -f foo &#x8207; --file foo &#x4e5f;&#x53ef;&#x4ee5;&#x5beb;&#x6210; -ffoo &#x8207; --file=foo (&#x6ce8;&#x610f; long option &#x7528;&#x7b49;&#x865f;&#x4e32;&#x63a5;)"/>
<node CREATED="1281580919851" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1704675939" MODIFIED="1286345686463" TEXT="Typically, a given option either takes an argument or it doesn&#x2019;t.">
<font NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
<node CREATED="1281593210446" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_993766683" MODIFIED="1301459175377" TEXT="Lots of people want an &#x201c;optional option arguments&#x201d; feature, meaning that some options will take an argument if they see it, and won&#x2019;t if they don&#x2019;t.">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
