<node CREATED="1279833382959" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1514071514" MODIFIED="1284300068098" TEXT="info()">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
<node CREATED="1284300479813" ID="ID_1820977095" MODIFIED="1284300481517" TEXT="Overview">
<node CREATED="1284299871651" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_51512826" MODIFIED="1284300502079" TEXT="Returns an instance of the class mimetools.Message containing meta-information associated with the URL.">
<node CREATED="1279835689666" ID="ID_777217289" MODIFIED="1279839555671" TEXT="&gt;&gt;&gt; import urllib&#xa;&gt;&gt;&gt; info = urllib.urlopen(&apos;http://www.google.com&apos;).info()&#xa;&gt;&gt;&gt; type(info)&#xa;&lt;type &apos;instance&apos;&gt; # &#x600e;&#x9ebc;&#x53c8;&#x662f; instance?&#xa;&gt;&gt;&gt; dir(info)&#xa;[&apos;__contains__&apos;, &apos;__delitem__&apos;, &apos;__doc__&apos;, &apos;__getitem__&apos;, &apos;__init__&apos;, &apos;__iter__&apos;, &apos;__len__&apos;, &apos;__module__&apos;, &apos;__setitem__&apos;, &apos;__str__&apos;, &apos;addcontinue&apos;, &apos;addheader&apos;, &apos;dict&apos;, &apos;encodingheader&apos;, &apos;fp&apos;, &apos;get&apos;, &apos;getaddr&apos;, &apos;getaddrlist&apos;, &apos;getallmatchingheaders&apos;, &apos;getdate&apos;, &apos;getdate_tz&apos;, &apos;getencoding&apos;, &apos;getfirstmatchingheader&apos;, &apos;getheader&apos;, &apos;getheaders&apos;, &apos;getmaintype&apos;, &apos;getparam&apos;, &apos;getparamnames&apos;, &apos;getplist&apos;, &apos;getrawheader&apos;, &apos;getsubtype&apos;, &apos;gettype&apos;, &apos;has_key&apos;, &apos;headers&apos;, &apos;iscomment&apos;, &apos;isheader&apos;, &apos;islast&apos;, &apos;items&apos;, &apos;keys&apos;, &apos;maintype&apos;, &apos;parseplist&apos;, &apos;parsetype&apos;, &apos;plist&apos;, &apos;plisttext&apos;, &apos;readheaders&apos;, &apos;rewindbody&apos;, &apos;seekable&apos;, &apos;setdefault&apos;, &apos;startofbody&apos;, &apos;startofheaders&apos;, &apos;status&apos;, &apos;subtype&apos;, &apos;type&apos;, &apos;typeheader&apos;, &apos;unixfrom&apos;, &apos;values&apos;]&#xa;"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1284299883561" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_20345373" MODIFIED="1284300038487" TEXT="When the method is HTTP, these headers are those returned by the server at the head of the retrieved HTML page (including Content-Length and Content-Type). &#x53ef;&#x4ee5;&#x9032;&#x4e00;&#x6b65;&#x900f;&#x904e; headers &#x8207; getheader(name) &#x53d6;&#x5f97; Headers">
<node CREATED="1279839582841" ID="ID_447617700" MODIFIED="1279839997645" TEXT="&gt;&gt;&gt; import urllib&#xa;&gt;&gt;&gt; info = urllib.urlopen(&apos;http://www.google.com&apos;)&#xa;&gt;&gt;&gt; print info.headers, type(info.headers)&#xa;[&apos;Date: Thu, 22 Jul 2010 22:58:32 GMT\r\n&apos;, &apos;Expires: -1\r\n&apos;, &apos;Cache-Control: private, max-age=0\r\n&apos;, &apos;Content-Type: text/html; charset=Big5\r\n&apos;, &apos;Set-Cookie: PREF=ID=fc5aedee4edb2275:TM=1279839512:LM=1279839512:S=MS-VRMGjxVLtCOi5; expires=Sat, 21-Jul-2012 22:58:32 GMT; path=/; domain=.google.com.tw\r\n&apos;, &apos;Set-Cookie: NID=37=Rf4nuvVIkMSUYstowZVnMa8gbvSQb4_8fXyfncW7tSOcmHelK1g95CgMpTek-ip1XjqTb5Uq6sk-D4_sAxo6iPkj6CeGcZAwkkOp6mGWtgGlBfQQvgLjlpWEjumm4So9; expires=Fri, 21-Jan-2011 22:58:32 GMT; path=/; domain=.google.com.tw; HttpOnly\r\n&apos;, &apos;Server: gws\r\n&apos;, &apos;X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block\r\n&apos;] &lt;type &apos;list&apos;&gt;&#xa;&gt;&gt;&gt; print info.getheader(&apos;Content-Type&apos;), info.getheader(&apos;content-type&apos;) # Header &#x540d;&#x7a31;&#x4e0d;&#x5206;&#x5927;&#x5c0f;&#x5beb;&#xa;text/html; charset=Big5 text/html; charset=Big5"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1284299896082" ID="ID_971531941" MODIFIED="1284299911870" TEXT="When the method is FTP, a Content-Length header will be present if (as is now usual) the server passed back a file length in response to the FTP retrieval request."/>
<node CREATED="1284299912118" ID="ID_530396271" MODIFIED="1284299923475" TEXT="A Content-Type header will be present if the MIME type can be guessed."/>
<node CREATED="1284299923717" ID="ID_918939381" MODIFIED="1284299939097" TEXT="When the method is local-file, returned headers will include a Date representing the file&#x2019;s last-modified time, a Content-Length giving file size, and a Content-Type containing a guess at the file&#x2019;s type."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1284300483168" ID="ID_1550269501" MODIFIED="1284300508506" TEXT="Returns: mimetools.Message"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1279833388136" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_225368844" MODIFIED="1279838445718" TEXT="getcode()">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
<node CREATED="1284300572317" ID="ID_503379757" MODIFIED="1284300586223" TEXT="Returns the HTTP status code that was sent with the response, or None if the URL is no HTTP URL."/>
<node CREATED="1284300588138" ID="ID_809614497" MODIFIED="1284300605192" TEXT="Returns: status code (string) or None"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1279833390736" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_620307305" MODIFIED="1279838446284" TEXT="geturl()">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
<node CREATED="1284300516964" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1450929497" MODIFIED="1284300518728" TEXT="Overview">
<node CREATED="1284300074003" ID="ID_1611472951" MODIFIED="1284300080826" TEXT="Returns the real URL of the page."/>
<node CREATED="1284300100493" ID="ID_1549168553" MODIFIED="1284300116896" TEXT="In some cases, the HTTP server redirects a client to another URL. The urlopen() function handles this transparently, but in some cases the caller needs to know which URL the client was redirected to. The geturl() method can be used to get at this redirected URL."/>
<node CREATED="1279838855571" ID="ID_899731149" MODIFIED="1279838931264" TEXT="&gt;&gt;&gt; import urllib&#xa;&gt;&gt;&gt; url = urllib.urlopen(&apos;http://www.yahoo.com.tw&apos;)&#xa;&gt;&gt;&gt; print url.geturl()&#xa;http://tw.yahoo.com/ &lt;-- &#x8ddf;&#x539f;&#x4f86;&#x7684; URL &#x4e0d;&#x540c;"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1284300518948" ID="ID_284664963" MODIFIED="1284300550581" TEXT="Returns: a string, redirected URL."/>
</node>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1284298968898" ID="ID_1514296632" MODIFIED="1284299011943" TEXT="Raises: IOError, if the connection cannot be made."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1284245945184" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1769961103" MODIFIED="1284245950232" TEXT="urlretrive(url)">
<node CREATED="1284245961046" ID="ID_748803061" MODIFIED="1284245992811" TEXT="Copy a network object denoted by a URL to a local file, if necessary. If the URL points to a local file, or a valid cached copy of the object exists, the object is not copied. (&#x6ce8;&#x610f;&#x9019;&#x88e1; &quot;if necessary&quot; &#x7684;&#x8aaa;&#x6cd5;)"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1279862348549" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_604002615" MODIFIED="1284301530845" TEXT="urlencode(query)">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="Monospaced" SIZE="12"/>
<node CREATED="1284301576755" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_423780894" MODIFIED="1284301578278" TEXT="Overview">
<node CREATED="1284301580912" ID="ID_1114946154" MODIFIED="1284301910916" TEXT="Convert a mapping object or a sequence of two-element tuples to a &#x201c;url-encoded&#x201d; string, suitable to pass to urlopen() above as the optional data argument. When a sequence of two-element tuples is used as the query argument, the first element of each tuple is a key and the second is a value."/>
<node CREATED="1284301605553" ID="ID_974349981" MODIFIED="1284301908546" TEXT="This is useful to pass a dictionary of form fields to a POST request. The resulting string is a series of key=value pairs separated by &apos;&amp;&apos; characters, where both key and value are quoted using quote_plus() above."/>
<node CREATED="1279865000583" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1914449791" MODIFIED="1279865002094" TEXT="Examples">
<node CREATED="1279865236996" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1129855196" MODIFIED="1279865238266" TEXT="Mapping">
<node CREATED="1279865208594" ID="ID_551356597" MODIFIED="1279865231533" TEXT="&gt;&gt;&gt; map = { &apos;k1&apos;: &apos;v1&apos;, &apos;k2&apos;: [ &apos;v2-1&apos;, &apos;v2-2&apos; ] }&#xa;&gt;&gt;&gt; urllib.urlencode(map)&#xa;&apos;k2=%5B%27v2-1%27%2C+%27v2-2%27%5D&amp;k1=v1&apos; &lt;-- &#x6574;&#x500b; List &#x90fd;&#x88ab;&#x7de8;&#x9032;&#x53bb;&#x4e86;, &#x770b;&#x4e0d;&#x61c2;?&#xa;&gt;&gt;&gt; urllib.urlencode(map, False)&#xa;&apos;k2=%5B%27v2-1%27%2C+%27v2-2%27%5D&amp;k1=v1&apos;&#xa;&gt;&gt;&gt; urllib.urlencode(map, True)&#xa;&apos;k2=v2-1&amp;k2=v2-2&amp;k1=v1&apos;&#xa;"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1279865334976" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1831638734" MODIFIED="1279865351563" TEXT="Sequence">
<node CREATED="1279865337131" ID="ID_1122354800" MODIFIED="1279865338829" TEXT="&gt;&gt;&gt; lst = [ (&apos;k1&apos;, &apos;v1&apos;), (&apos;k2&apos;, [ &apos;v2-1&apos;, &apos;v2-2&apos; ]) ]&#xa;&gt;&gt;&gt; urllib.urlencode(lst)&#xa;&apos;k1=v1&amp;k2=%5B%27v2-1%27%2C+%27v2-2%27%5D&apos;&#xa;&gt;&gt;&gt; urllib.urlencode(lst, False)&#xa;&apos;k1=v1&amp;k2=%5B%27v2-1%27%2C+%27v2-2%27%5D&apos;&#xa;&gt;&gt;&gt; urllib.urlencode(lst, True)&#xa;&apos;k1=v1&amp;k2=v2-1&amp;k2=v2-2&apos;&#xa;"/>
</node>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1279864757133" ID="ID_1677167592" MODIFIED="1279864759456" TEXT="Parameters">
<node CREATED="1279864765061" ID="ID_261629488" MODIFIED="1284301827257" TEXT="query (mapping or sequence of key-value pairs)"/>
<node CREATED="1279864766407" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_542158013" MODIFIED="1284301779919" TEXT="doseq (boolean)">
<node CREATED="1284301710105" ID="ID_1736610449" MODIFIED="1284301760944" TEXT="The value element in itself can be a sequence and in that case, if the optional parameter doseq is evaluates to True, individual key=value pairs separated by &apos;&amp;&apos; are generated for each element of the value sequence for the key. The order of parameters in the encoded string will match the order of parameter tuples in the sequence."/>
<node CREATED="1279864769437" ID="ID_1907401554" MODIFIED="1279864996005" TEXT="Mapping &#x6216; Sequence &#x7684; Value Element &#x4e5f;&#x53ef;&#x4ee5;&#x662f;&#x53e6;&#x5916;&#x4e00;&#x500b; Sequence; &#x9019;&#x500b;&#x53c3;&#x6578;&#x70ba; True &#x6642;, &#x6bcf;&#x4e00;&#x500b; Element &#x90fd;&#x6703;&#x7522;&#x751f;&#x4e00;&#x500b; key=value, &#x9019;&#x500b;&#x53c3;&#x6578;&#x70ba; False &#x6642;, &#x53ea;&#x6703;&#x8f38;&#x51fa;&#x7b2c;&#x4e00;&#x500b; Element"/>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1284301930142" ID="ID_1562565207" MODIFIED="1284301954520" TEXT="Returns: URL-encoded string."/>
</node>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1281695477220" ID="ID_1425831883" LINK="http://docs.python.org/library/urllib2.html" MODIFIED="1290740325102" TEXT="urllib2 (STD)">
<node CREATED="1281943685264" ID="ID_583117808" MODIFIED="1281943686751" TEXT="Overview">
<node CREATED="1282008232336" ID="ID_132445702" MODIFIED="1282013204186" TEXT="Help in opening URLs (mostly HTTP) in a complex world &#x2014; basic and digest authentication, redirections, cookies and more. &#x56e0;&#x70ba;&#x5b83;&#x652f;&#x63f4;&#x5f88;&#x591a;&#x7684; Handler, &#x5176;&#x4e2d; Digest Authentication &#x8207; Cookies &#x5c31;&#x662f;&#x900f;&#x904e; HTTPDigestAuthHandler &#x8207; HTTPCookieProcessor &#x4f86;&#x652f;&#x63f4;"/>
<node CREATED="1282015102863" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_858320151" MODIFIED="1282025217302" TEXT="&#x6700;&#x91cd;&#x8981;&#x7684;&#x5169;&#x500b;&#x6982;&#x5ff5;&#x662f; Opener &#x8207; Handler">
<node CREATED="1282025217859" ID="ID_1697342294" MODIFIED="1282025217859" TEXT="Opener &#x672c;&#x8eab;&#x53ef;&#x4ee5;&#x8a3b;&#x518a;&#x8a31;&#x591a; Handlers, &#x4e0d;&#x540c;&#x7684; Protocols &#x7531;&#x4e0d;&#x540c;&#x7684; Handlers &#x8655;&#x7406; (&#x4f8b;&#x5982; HTTPHandler, FTPHandler &#x7b49;)"/>
