<node CREATED="1300960973598" ID="ID_1180677836" MODIFIED="1300961021512" TEXT="`build_opener()` provides many handlers by default, including a `ProxyHandler`. By default, `ProxyHandler` uses the environment variables named `&lt;scheme&gt;_proxy`, where `&lt;scheme&gt;` is the URL scheme involved. For example, the `http_proxy` environment variable is read to obtain the HTTP proxy&#x2019;s URL.&#xff08;HTTPS &#x5247;&#x8981;&#x53e6;&#x5916;&#x8a2d;&#x5b9a;&#x4e00;&#x500b; `https_proxy`&#xff09;"/>
<node CREATED="1300961052155" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_131502888" MODIFIED="1300961186726" TEXT="This example replaces the default `ProxyHandler` with one that uses &apos;&apos;programmatically-supplied&apos;&apos;&#xff08;&#x76f8;&#x5c0d;&#x65bc;&#x5f9e; environment variables &#x53d6;&#x5f97;&#x8a2d;&#x5b9a;&#x800c;&#x8a00;&#xff09; proxy URLs, and adds proxy authorization support with `ProxyBasicAuthHandler`.">
<node CREATED="1300961135937" ID="ID_94243927" MODIFIED="1300961137625" TEXT="proxy_handler = urllib2.ProxyHandler({&apos;http&apos;: &apos;http://www.example.com:3128/&apos;})&#xa;proxy_auth_handler = urllib2.ProxyBasicAuthHandler()&#xa;proxy_auth_handler.add_password(&apos;realm&apos;, &apos;host&apos;, &apos;username&apos;, &apos;password&apos;)&#xa;&#xa;opener = urllib2.build_opener(proxy_handler, proxy_auth_handler)&#xa;# This time, rather than install the OpenerDirector, we use it directly:&#xa;opener.open(&apos;http://www.example.com/login.html&apos;)&#xa;"/>
</node>
